features: 【Fit perfectly】The Ram 1500 Stake Pocket Cover is compatible with Dodge Ram 2019 2020 2021 2022. Do not fit 2018 Ram and before. In addition,our Ram 2500 Stake Pocket Cover is created according to the precise data by laser measurement. Therefore,it fit the rear stake pocket holes perfectly. Please measure the size of stake pocket match the product.Please make sure it is compatible with your car hole size before purchasing.

【High Quality Materials】This Ram stake pocket cover is made of ABS plastic,which provided the cover with abrasion and corrosion resistance.Moreover,the stake pocket cover does not fade and crack. For another,there is no color difference between the cover caps and the bed rail after installation.

【Well protection】The 2022 Ram stake pocket cover is enable to protect the stake hole from exposing. It make an influence on keeping rain,snow,dirt,leaves and sand out of the stake hole. Therefore,the ram stake pocket cover is a good choice to prevent the stake hole from rusting.

【Custom-made Design】The Bed rail caps Hole Plugs compatible with Dodge ram 2019-2022 makes Your Car look more refined.There is an uneven edge at the extend of stake pocket cover, which could make the bed rail cover better fit the hole of original rail hole. The durable and sturdy Ram stake pocket covers can not only protect the stake hole, but also give your truck a great custom look.

【Easy Installation】Dodge Ram 1500 stake pockets covers installation will be extremely easy and convenient,just for one minute. Wash and clean the hole firstly. Simply place the stake pocket cover over the stake pocket hole. Then snap the stake pockets covers in to hole. The whole installation process does not require any tools. And with the free Reinforced Cutton Mat: Comes with a non-slip cutton mat to make it Fit tight & Prevent Bounce out.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stake Pocket Covers for 2021 Silverado
reviews.reviewText: I'm glad I read several customer reviews on this product before purchasing it. It's a challenge to get the cover completely pressed in place. It was in the mid 40s outside, so the plastic cover was stiff but not frozen. I wouldn't want to try to install it if it was really cold outside. I had to remove the tape from the covers and use a rubber hammer to gently tap the edges to get the cover into place. As you can see in the attached picture, it isn't flush with the side rails. That's fine with me. It looks good.
